cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper deals with deep neural networks and their performance in image classification tasks, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Given that the paper proposes a noise-tolerant training algorithm for DNNs using synthetic noisy labels, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the experiments are conducted on image datasets, it is also likely to belong to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The other sub-categories are less likely but still possible depending on the specific details of the paper.
